    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You're trained in martial weapons. If your deity's favored weapon is a simple weapon or an unarmed attack, you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.feats-srd.DfLkIIg2reyYW3a8]{Deadly Simplicity} cleric feat. You gain the rogue's @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.classfeatures.j1JE61quDxdge4mg]{Sneak Attack} class feature. Your Sneak Attack damage applies to your deity's favored weapon, even if it would not normally qualify. Instead of increasing the damage dice for your sneak attack at 5th, 11th, and 17th levels, it increases by one dice at 9th and 17th level. You're trained in light armor. At 13th level, if you gain the @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.classfeatures.0mJTp4LdEHBLInoe]{Divine Defense} class feature, you also gain expert proficiency in light armor. You have expert proficiency in Reflex saves.</p>",
